org.cougaar.util
Class RarelyModifiedList

java.lang.Object
  org.cougaar.util.RarelyModifiedList
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable, java.util.Collection, java.util.List
public class RarelyModifiedList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.List, java.io.Serializable

A "double buffered" List implementation, optimized for cases where the contents rarely change. This implementation acts superficially like a normal list except that it actually is implemented by always creating a new private copy of the list on each modification. This allows iteration and such to never have to worry about comodification exceptions. The downside is that it is relatively expensive to modify the contents.
